its convenience it has also began to flounder. now any one who has the capability to make this new Uber armor from the moon is definitly set for life, its a money maker, and a time consumer as well. <br><br><br>The first peice of HE cultur armor i was talking about, when i first looked for it all, the ingredients, took me 4 days, and then i failed it but thats besides the point =P.<br><br>I guess what i am really trying to say here is that, i am disapointed with the change in the Fine Plate trivial lvls, I really wish there would have been more warning, maybe i had my eyes close, i dont know, it hit me like a ton of bricks, out of no where, from another smith. <br><br>One day, i will be at the top, with the best of the smithers, it is my dream, and i am more than half way there, although the second half is always the hardest when it comes to trade skills. But if anyone is wanting to start smithing, realize that this road is a hard and discaplined one. You will want to quite, you will want to throw in the smithy hammer and say **********ing***********er. And you will spend hours trying to get everything together to make some Fine plate, and when your done you may only make 200p or so. Smithing isnt really about people buying your ability, they buy your time, cuase thats what you spend the most of. Money, not to much at higher lvls, people pay well, its your time they are buying, your time you took to get that good, the time you took to get all the material, the time you took to take the order, and all the time you lost that you could have been Lvling and instead were dilligently hammering away at the sweaty mercy of your forge wherever in norrath you may be. <br><br>I am not sure why i right this, but i just want some one to know, anyone who cares, smiths are people just like you, smithing hasnt been a very popular thing until the money items came out. now smithing is like jeweling, just a way to make money, but i do it becuase i love it, Back in the day mak