ou a bunch of platinum for porting them to North Karana, but if you take them to Cobalt Scar on short notice, you'll probably get a nice donation.  I knew a wizard that would bind in Katta Castellum and make nearly 200 pp per TL for people who were nearby and didn't want to run back to the Nexus when they had to go raid on Norrath.  And most of the time she never even quoted a price, they just gave it to her.<br><br>Honestly smithing in EQ is pretty much fucked at this point.  Even if you do have the cash to make fine plate, supply has so far outstripped demand for that level of armor that you're not going to make much of a profit on it.  Likewise with other smithed armor except the brand new stuff.  If the game had item decay, things would be different perhaps, but since items stay around forever...well you get the idea.  Who wants to pay 100-150 pp for a fine plate bp when they can pick up a comparable dropped bp with stats on it for close to the same price?  I'd put the time in to gather stuff to make an item, even farm cash to buy what I needed, if I had people placing orders with me to fill.  I'd rather not have something sit in my bank for a week before I can sell it, I have enough crap in there as it is.<br><br>For now I'll just keep puttering away at smithing in my spare time, and maybe i'll get it to 250 some day, but I think the odds of that happening before I quit EQ for a newer game are slim at this point. <br><br>For Xaasf:<br><br>Most classes have a chain and a plate variant.  As far as I know though, only high elves (and maybe dark elves) have caster-useable chains.  All other caster-usable crafted armor is done through tailoring.  Let's not even talk about how fucked tailoring is.  At least in smithing you can buy 70% of your components if you can somehow find the money...in tailoring half of what you need for the good stuff is a rare drop from a rare spawn.<br> <p><p align=center><b>Talaen Nephele<br>Cavalier of the Nameless<br>Guildleader